arried me to Lenton station, Lenton used to have a station at those days and I can remember them carrying me. And my mother just - waving her hand, and an apron on - you know, saying goodbye to me, that was when I was - four. And I can remember everything
 
I had on that day, yet I can't remember much - and I remember landing at - Gillingham we went to first - remember getting there and then me aunt and uncle got a house in New Brompton, that's Chatham district like. But he was - secretary of the Trades Club
. He worked in Chatham Dockyard. Me Uncle, yes. See?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11943414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5993906\charrsid12812171 It obviously had a marked effect on you to remember all that detail?
