hort of work you know, as they were in the lace trade. But I can't remember him actually out of work, but I do remember them saying once when I wasn't at home that he was out of work and - my mother and father - started a - a coffee stall. There was none 
that - was in full swing at Beeston. They used to go and stand outside at six o'clock in the morning to sell hot coffee and tea. Things like that, anything to - help you see. And they all - they christened my father King Coffee, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11943414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5993906\charrsid12812171 Was he ever ill?
