Yes, until - I was there about - two and a half years I think. And - then I retired, to be very candid. And - I gave me home up, 'cos I was so tired of being on me own, I gave me home up, all but - 
well not just what I've got, I had to buy quite a bit but - I got a full home and I gave it all up and went to live with a sister-in-law. And I - got on very well but I got homesickness you see, wanted a place of me own - so I got a little cottage. 'Cours
e
 they pulled it down, put me in this you see. Well - then I got at home - I was at home for a while, and I got fed up with being a - nothing to do, I've always been very active you see. And I went to Everlastic. Beeston, yes. Yes, foundation garments. And
 I went there and - I was there for fourteen years. Then - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11943414 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5993906\charrsid12812171 Looking back on the jobs you've had would you have preferred another type of occupation do you think?
